nding with reflections on today’s globalization. Along the way, he considers how the interplay of geography, technology, and institutions influenced the Neolithic revolution; the role of the horse in the emergence of empires; the spread of large land-based empires in the classical age; the rise of global empires after the opening of sea routes from Europe to Asia and the Americas; and the industrial age. The dynamics of these past waves, Sachs demonstrates, offer fresh perspective on the ongoing processes taking place in our own time—a globalization based on digital technologies. Sachs emphasizes the need for new methods of international governance and cooperation to prevent conflicts and to achieve economic, social, and environmental objectives aligned with sustainable development. The Ages of Globalization is a vital book for all readers aiming to make sense of our rapidly changing world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aEconomic history. 0aGlobalizationxHistory. 0aWorld history. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Globalization.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2019z978311065195908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2020z9783110704594oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472340uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/sach1937440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231550482423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780231550482.jpg  a978-3-11-065195-9  CUP eBook-Package Pilot Project 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Engli